node.description:
â€˜Acid Dropâ€™ is a limited NFT collection released today to celebrate 303 Day, the synthesizer at the heart of Richie Hawtinâ€™s trademark Plastikman sound. Available as five individual editions, four of which are limited to 33 each and one open to auction, â€˜Acid Dropâ€™ is inspired by Hawtinâ€™s first album as Plastikman, â€˜Sheet Oneâ€™ recorded in 1993.

The NFT is based on the original image of Richie Hawtin's Roland TB-303 used to create the iconic album. Each of the original melody patterns, signalled by the flashing red lights, have been stored in this particular 303 for the last 27 years with a number of battery changes along the way. As each TB-303 has its own unique character, Hawtin's 303 is the only one that truly sounds like Plastikman. This image was taken and processed by Richie Hawtin and includes the dry signal of the acid line from five tracks, as if this NFT contains the basic blueprint or DNA of Plastikman.
node.name: Plastikman "Acid Drop - Sheet One"

This is a rolling drop collection: a different kind of binaural beat will be dropped once the former sells out. There are a total of five types (Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, and Theta). Once all of them are dropped & sold, we'll present a surprise valuable drop that will be that our collectors will get first access to!

Binaural Beats are a well-documented aid in encouraging healthy brain function, especially when used in meditation. They work by placing a pure tone in one ear and a different one in the other. The resulting "beats" are interpreted by the brain as a single frequency. This encourages the brain to oscillate at this frequency, producing the desired effect. *Headphones are required
